column28: Doors collapsing? Cables were slack, skipper thought due to large waves, reducing our catch
Lots of mud; net cut to remove branch; net torn on stanchion (4-5' tear)
Halfway through, had to increase speed to keep doors from crossing, looked like they were rolled up.
Big rock ripped a small hole.
Towed good, looked good, light haul.
Skipper says to stay south of center point at this station.
2 kt current pulling hard. Trying to stay out of rip seems to help. Turned out clean but light.
